title: UMD Progressing to When It Matters Most
text:
UMD Progressing to When It Matters Most 
By Zach Schneider October 20, 2015 Updated Oct 20, 2015 at 6:38 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) football team is coming off perhaps its most complete game of the season, and no one is concerned that it came against a winless University of Mary squad. 
The Bulldogs beat Mary 45-0 this past Saturday, and head coach Curt Wiese said it was a good step in trying to prepare for a possible berth in the NCAA Division II tournament. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
This weekend, UMD has another winless opponent, and Wiese expects a similar step forward. 
"We know we're going to get Crookston's best game of the year," he said. "This game and this week are about our team getting better. One of our goals at the start of the season was to make sure we are playing our best football at the end of the year." 
UMD has won 14 straight games at Malosky Stadium and will kick off against Minnesota-Crookston at 1:05 p.m. on Saturday. That game can be seen live in the Northland on the My 9 Sports Network.
